HEADWORD: Bromism
<hw>Bro"mism</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A
diseased condition produced by the excessive use of bromine or one of
its compounds. It is characterized by mental dullness and muscular
weakness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bromize</ent>⟦br⟧
